'''''Microlarinus lareynii''''' (commonly known as '''''Puncturevine Seed Weevil''''')<ref name="Entomological Society of America - puncturevine seed weevil">{{cite web|url=http://www.entsoc.org/puncturevine-seed-weevil-1|title=puncturevine seed weevil|publisher=[[Entomological Society of America]]|accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref> is a [[weevil]] of the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Curculionidae]].<ref name="ITIS - ITIS standard report - Microlarinus lareynii  (Jacquelin du Val, 1852)">{{cite web|url=https://www.itis.gov/servlet/SingleRpt/SingleRpt?search_topic=TSN&search_value=187917|title=ITIS standard report - Microlarinus lareynii  (Jacquelin du Val, 1852)|publisher=[[Integrated Taxonomic Information System]]|accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref>  It is [[endemicism|native]] to interior regions of Italy, France and [[Rajasthan]] in India.<ref name="Ministry of Forests, Lands and Natural Resource Operations (British Columbia) - Microlarinus lareynii (Jacquelin duVal)">{{cite web|url=http://www.for.gov.bc.ca/hra/plants/biocontrol/detailed_bioagent_pages/Microlarinus_lareynii.htm|title=Microlarinus lareynii (Jacquelin duVal)|work=[[Ministry of Forests, Lands and Natural Resource Operations (British Columbia)]]|publisher=[[Government of British Columbia]]|accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref>

Microlarinus lareynii feeds on the seeds of the puncturevine, ''[[Tribulus terrestris]]''. Together with [[Microlarinus lypriformis]], which feeds on the stems of the puncturevine, it has been introduced as a [[Biological pest control#Biological control agents|biological control agent]] in the [[United States of America]]<ref name="University of California Statewide Integrated Pest Management Program - Puncturevine  (Tribulus terrestris) ">{{cite web|url=http://www.ipm.ucdavis.edu/PMG/WEEDS/puncturevine.html|title=Puncturevine  (Tribulus terrestris)|work=University of California Statewide Integrated Pest Management Program|publisher=[[University of California, Davis]]|accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref> and [[Canada]].<ref name="Ministry of Forests, Lands and Natural Resource Operations (British Columbia) - Microlarinus lareynii (Jacquelin duVal)"/>

